### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = tu_token_aqui_despues_del_login

### 1. Probar servidor
GET {{baseUrl}}

### 2. Login del dueño
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@migym.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 3. Verificar token (reemplazar TOKEN con el que obtuviste)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Obtener estadísticas
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/clients/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Crear cliente
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/clients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "nombre": "Juan",
  "apellido": "Pérez",
  "email": "juan@gmail.com",
  "documento": "12345678",
  "telefono": "+54911234567",
  "montoMensual": 3500
}

### 6. Obtener todos los clientes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/clients?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Buscar clientes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/clients?search=juan
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Filtrar por estado
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/clients?status=pagado
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Marcar cliente como pagado (reemplazar ID)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/clients/CLIENTE_ID/payment
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "estadoPago": "pagado"
}

### 10. Obtener pagos vencidos
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/overdue
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}